# Netlify _redirects
# Empty file: any URL not matching a static file gets Netlify's default
# 404 (no SPA rewrite). Static files (robots.txt, sitemap.xml, sw.js,
# manifest.webmanifest, /icons/*, /legacy/*, /quizzes/*, /lessons/*,
# /favicon.svg, /apple-touch-icon.png, /favicon-32.png, etc.) are
# served from the publish directory with their correct Content-Type.
#
# The SvelteKit client-side router handles navigation between
# /escola/, /biblioteca/, etc. without needing server-side rewrites,
# so we don't need a /* → /index.html rule here.